{{Houʻeiki|fakanofo= Tuʻi Tonga |ʻaho fakanofo= ~1400 |ʻaho fakamālōlō= |ki muʻa= [[Havea I]] |hoko= [[Lomiʻaetupuʻa]] |}}
{{Kāinga ofi|faʻahinga=fale ʻalo |maama= tangata |tamai= [[Havea I]] |faʻē= |ʻaho fanauʻi= ~1400 |ʻaho pekia= |taʻokete-tokoua= {{tokoua|||||||||}} |taʻokete-lau= {{tokoua|||||||||}} |tehina-tokoua= {{tokoua|[[Nganatatafu]]||||||||}} |ʻohoana1=? |fānau1= {{tokoua|[[Lomiʻaetupuʻa]]||||||||}} |}}*E.W. Gifford, Tongan myths and tales, Bernice Pauahi Bishop museum bulletin '''8''', 1924 ʻOku ui ia ʻi he talanoa ʻe taha pē kia Tatafu-mei-Muʻa (tangata tatau ?). Ko ia mo hono tehina ko Nganatatafu, naʻe ʻeva kinaua ki he fineʻeiki hoihoifua ʻi Haʻamoa, ko Hina.
ʻOku pehē foki ʻe he taha ko Lomiʻaetupuʻa, naʻe ʻikai hono foha, kā ko hono mokopuna pē, naʻe ʻi ai ko hono foha '''Nganaʻeiki''' mo ʻene fineʻeiki ko Hina mei [[Haʻamoa]], pea hona foha pē ko Lomiʻaetupuʻa ia.
Pea ʻoku pehē ʻe he taha ko Nganaʻeiki ko e taʻokete ʻo Nganatatafu ia.
{{English|translation}}

