{{Houʻeiki|fakanofo= Tuʻihaʻangana |ʻaho fakanofo= ~1400 |ʻaho fakamālōlō= |ki muʻa= (ʻuluaki) |hoko= [[Havea Hikuleʻo I]] |}}
{{Kāinga ofi|faʻahinga=houʻeiki |maama= tangata |tamai= [[Havea I]] |faʻē= |ʻaho fanauʻi= ~1400 |ʻaho pekia= |taʻokete-tokoua= {{tokoua|[[Tatafuʻeikimeimuʻa]]|Nganaʻeiki|||||||}} |taʻokete-lau= {{tokoua|&nbsp;|&nbsp;|||||||}} |tehina-tokoua= {{tokoua|||||||||}} |ʻohoana1= (fefine [[Fisi]] ?) |fānau1= {{tokoua|[[Havea Hikuleʻo I]]||||||||}} |}}*E.W. Gifford, Tongan myths and tales, BPB '''8''', 1924 Naʻe nofo ʻa Nganatatafu ʻi [[Haʻano]]. Naʻe maʻu ia ʻa e ʻatu ʻuluaki ʻi Tongá ni mei he fineʻeiki Haʻamoa fakaʻofoʻofa, ko Hina. ʻOku pehē ko e tupuʻanga ia ʻo e [[:category:Tuʻihaʻangana|Tuʻihaʻangana]].
Mahalo pē ko Havea ʻoku ʻikai ko e ʻeiki, kā ko e kui pē ʻo ongo Ngana (tamai ko ʻEiki Tatafu mei [[Muʻa]]). Mahalo pē ko ʻEikitatafu ʻeni ʻoku tatau mo Tatafumeimuʻa ʻoku tatau mo [[Tatafuʻeikimeimuʻa]] (vakai ʻi hē). {{English|translation}}

