Neongo he taʻane ʻo Tuʻutanga mo ha Tuʻi Tonga, mahalo pē ʻUluakimata, kae ʻoku ʻikai pau, naʻe ʻikai ha [[moheofo]] ia, kā ko e fokonofo pē.
Ko Paku, naʻe hoko ia ko e toutai ʻo e Tuʻi Tonga. Ko hono hako ʻoku ʻiloa ko [[:Category:Fakafānua|Fakafānua]]
{{English|translation}}

It is said that Mataelehaʻamea had a war with [[Vaea]], (not his brother but the [[:Category:Tuʻi Haʻatakalaua|Tuʻi Haʻatakalaua]]), yet still married a daughter of him.
His younger brother Vuna was sent away to become governor of [[:Category:Vavaʻu|Vavaʻu]].
Another younger brother, Hafoka became governor for central [[Tongatapu]]. He founded a new clan, the [[:Category:Haʻa Havea lahi|Haʻa Havea lahi]], which in due time would become bitter opponents of the original [[:Category:Tuʻi Kanokupolu|Tuʻi Kanokupolu]] clan. {{Foki||Mataelehaʻamea}}

