|ʻohoana2=[[Hinehinaʻatelangi]]
|fānau2= {{tokoua|[[Tungīmānaʻia]]|Kulīkefu|||||||}}
|}}
Ko [[Tungīmānaʻia]] mo hono tehina, ko e tama kinaua ʻo [[Hinehinaʻatelangi]] pe [[Uliafu]]? ʻOku ʻikai pau.

{{Houʻeiki|fakanofo= Tuʻilakepa |ʻaho fakanofo= ~1675 pe ~1725 |ʻaho fakamālōlō= |ki muʻa= [[Nautu]] |hoko= [[Lātūnipuluʻiteafua]] |}}
{{Kāinga ofi|faʻahinga=houʻeiki |maama= tangata |tamai=[[Nautu]] |faʻē=[[Lelenoa]] |ʻaho fanauʻi= ~1675 pe ~1725 |ʻaho pekia= |taʻokete-tokoua= {{tokoua|[[Paleinangalu]]||||||||}} |taʻokete-lau= {{tokoua|&nbsp;||||||||}} |tehina-tokoua= {{tokoua||||||||||}} |ʻohoana1=[[Sinaitakalaʻifanakavakilangi]] |fānau1= {{tokoua|[[Lātūnipuluʻiteafua]]|[[Moʻungaolakepa]]|Lāpuloufisi||||||}} |}}*D.V. Burley; Sacred child and sacred place; Polynesian paradox, USP 2005; ISBN 982-02-0371-6 Mahalo pe ko Paleinangalu naʻe ʻikai hono taʻokete, ka hono tehina pē. Nofo ʻi [[Nukulau]], [[Fisi]].
Mahalo pē ʻoku ʻi ai ha hala ʻi he ngaahi tohi hokohoko. Kapau naʻe moʻui hono taʻokete [[Paleinangalu]] ʻi 1670, ko Fehokomoelangiʻifisi ʻi heni, mali mo [[Sinaitakalaʻifanakavakilangi]] moʻui he 1725, ko e foha pe mokopuna pe ʻo Fehokomoelangiʻifisi ko e tehina. {{English|translation}}

If [[Kafoamotalau]] was the oldest son of Vaea, of his first wife, then why did [[Moeakiola]], a younger brother, succeed their father? This only make sense if the latter ranked higher than the former because of the high rank of his mother. Then indeed [[Simuoko]] must have been a [[:category:tamahā|tamahā]], despite the denial of it by some.
*D.V. Burley; Sacred child and sacred place; Polynesian paradox, USP 2005; ISBN 982-02-0371-6
