{{Kāinga ofi
|faʻahinga=houʻeiki
|maama= tangata
|tamai= [[Vuki]]
|faʻē= Mafihape
|ʻaho fanauʻi= ~1800
|ʻaho pekia=
|taʻokete-tokoua= {{tokoua|||||||||}}
|taʻokete-lau= {{tokoua|||||||||}} 
|tehina-tokoua= {{tokoua|Lātūniua|Taumoepeau|Vuna|Moaeteau|Faingaʻanuku Fakatoulavea|Niumataevalu|||}}
|ʻohoana1= [[Luseane Halaevalu Mataʻaho]]
|fānau1= {{tokoua|[[ʻAnaseini Tupou Veihola]]|Vaohoi|Sione Talaumokafoa||||||}}
|}}http://web.archive.org/web/20030311031225/http://www.uq.net.au/~zzhsoszy/states/tonga/tuita.html

[[Siaosi Tupou I|Tāufaʻāhau]], Fīnau's older (step)brother, was quite angry with his mother, Hoamofaleono and her then husband Moimoiʻangahā about her having this child. He ordered it to be abandoned on the reefs of Vainī, to put it in the strong currents, to die. This would have been at [[Mataʻaho (Tongatapu)|Mataʻaho]], in the lagoon.
But that night Fīnau Alakihihifo, daughter of Kaufusituʻa Kumāikuvalu Maʻafu, (Hoamofaleono's brother?) took the child away and brought it in safety to [[Kolonga]] in the hands of Moimoiʻangahā. His brothers Langitoutai and Teʻehalakamu next brought it to [[Fakakakai]] on [[Haʻano]]. They themselves stayed and died there, but Fīnau Filimoeʻuli later returned to [[Vainī]] to become the next [[:Category:Maʻafu|Maʻafu]], the line since then known as Maʻafu-tuku-ʻi-ʻau-lahi.
Nevertheless, it is also claimed that Tāufaʻāhau knew and gave his blessing to the move to [[Fakakakai]], so that he would have claims on the island; (Faka-kakai = make (more) people). Indeed still today the southern part of [[Haʻano]] is government estate rather than belonging to the original line of the [[:Category:Tuʻihaʻangana|Tuʻihaʻangana]]. {{foki||Fīnau Filimoeʻulie}}

[[Image:Niuatoputapu.gif|right|thumb|350px|Niuatoputapu (motu)]] [[Image:Niuatoputapu tafahi tonga.jpg|thumb|Mape fakahisitōlia ʻo e motú ni mo [[Tafahi]]]] [[Image:Niuatoputapu group.jpg|thumb|ʻAta satelaite]] Ko e motu ʻo '''Niuatoputapu''', i [[Tonga]].
Ngaahi kolo * Falehau 15.945° S 173.729° W * Hihifo, (kolomuʻa) 15.954° S 173.758° W * Vaipoa 15.947° S 173.746° W Ngaahi motu siʻi * Hakautuʻutuʻu 15.934° S 173.743° W * Hungana 15.953° S 173.767° W * Nukuseilala 15.966° S 173.762° W * Sikaihaʻa 15.964° S 173.762° W * Tafuna 15.963° S 173.764° W * Tavili 15.958° S 173.766° W * Tuʻunga 15.964° S 173.764° W
Ko e ngaahi tofiʻa: *[[:Category:Tuʻi ʻo Tonga|Tuʻi ʻo Tonga]], ʻa ia ko e tuʻi fefine (Falehau, Hihifo) *[[:Category:Tangipā|Tangipā]] (Vaipoa) *[[:Category:Māʻatu|Māʻatu]] (vahe tonga, ko e konga lahi taha ʻo e motu). {{Feituʻu Tonga|15°96|173°74}}
{{potuʻi}}
[[Category:Ongo Niua]]

Ko e '''ʻAlotolu''' ko e ʻotu fetuʻu ʻe tolu, ko e ''belt of Orion'' ʻi he lea fakapilitānia. ʻOku tatau mo e [[Haʻamonga ʻa Maui]], kae naʻe ʻi ai ha matāpule ʻe taha, Lehāʻuli, naʻa ne tala ange: ko e tamai, ko e ʻalo, mo e laumālie māʻoniʻoni.

