{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name= Golden beard grass, Red cling grass |faitā=Starr 050315-5209 Chrysopogon aciculatus.jpg |faitālaulahi= 240px |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻitaha]] |ordo= [[poales]] |familia= [[mohuku]] |genus=Chrysopogon |species=aciculatus |fakamoʻoniʻanga= ([[Anders Jahan Retzius|Retz.]]) [[Carl Bernhard von Trinius|Trin.]] |fehokotaki= cs }}
[[Image:C. aciculatus by 00918.jpg|thumb|left|240px|''C. aciculatus'']] Ko e '''matapekepeka''' pe '''matamatapeka''' pe '''matamatamanu''' ko e faʻahinga mohuku ia mo e ngaahi tenga talatala. ʻOku pipiki ʻaupito ki he ngaahi vala. Ko hono ʻuhinga tatau: ''Rhaphis aciculata'' (Retz.) Desv. mo e ''Andropogon aciculatus'' Retz.
==Hingoa ʻi he ngaahi lea kehe== *mosie fisi ([[lea fakaniuē]]) *papapa ([[lea fakatahisi]]) *mānienie ʻula, piʻipiʻi, pilipili ʻula ([[lea fakahauaiʻi]]) *mutia tai, mutia vao ([[lea fakahaʻamoa]]) *matie kura, matie piripiri, mauku koʻekoʻe, tumu ʻenua, tuakura ([[lea fakakuki]]) *kase ([[lea fakafisi]])
==Tataku== *http://cookislands.bishopmuseum.org/species.asp?id=5933 *Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī *Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward *Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=Coral plant |faitā=J multifida ies.jpg |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[malpighiales]] |familia= [[EUPHORBIACEAE]] |genus=Jatropha |species=multifida |fakamoʻoniʻanga= [[Carolus Linnaeus|L.]] |fehokotaki= cs }} Ko e '''fiki papālangi''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia, aʻu mita ʻe 6 ʻi olunga. Naʻe ʻomi mei he [[ʻAmelika]] loto. Ko hono anga ko e pupunga ʻo e matalaʻiʻakau kulokula mo e lau vahevaheʻi.
==Ngaahi faʻahinga kehekehe== *[[fiki]] *[[fiki kulamūmū]]
==Tataku== *http://cookislands.bishopmuseum.org/species.asp?id=6294 *Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī *Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward *Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=Peregrina, Spicy jatropha |faitā=jatropha integerrima 4.jpg |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[malpighiales]] |familia= [[EUPHORBIACEAE]] |genus=Jatropha |species=integerrima |fakamoʻoniʻanga= [[Nicolaus Joseph von Jacquin|Jacq.]] |fehokotaki= cs }} Ko e '''fiki kulamūmū''' (hingoa taʻefakalakanga) ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia, aʻu mita ʻe 6 ʻi olunga. Naʻe ʻomi mei [[Kiupa]], naʻe ʻikai fuoloa. Neongo ko ia ʻoku manakoa ʻaupito ia ʻe he kakai Tonga ʻi honau ʻapi ngoue, koeʻuhi hono lahi matalaʻiʻakau kulamūmū, meimei kulokula, pea mo ʻenau tangitangi meimei lolotonga he taimi kotoa.
Ko e fuʻu ʻakaú ni, ʻoku ʻikai hano ngaahi foʻi fua, ʻoku kehe mei he [[fiki]] pe [[fiki kai]]. (tokanga: ʻoku fakakonā ʻa hano foʻi tenga). ʻA ia ko e hā e ʻuhinga ʻoku ui ''fiki''? Ko e ʻuhinga ko e [[fiki]] mo e [[fiki papālangi]] mo ʻeni ʻoku kau ki he kāinga ofi tatau: ko e ''Jatropha''. ==Ngaahi faʻahinga kehekehe== *[[fiki]] *[[fiki papālangi]]
==Tataku== *http://cookislands.bishopmuseum.org/species.asp?id=6293 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=Tamarind |faitā=Tamarindus indica, leaves, pod.jpg |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[fabales]] |familia= [[FABACEAE]] |genus=Tamarindus |species=indica |fakamoʻoniʻanga= [[Carolus Linnaeus|L.]] |fehokotaki= c }} [[File:Tamarindus indica, flowers&leaves.jpg|thumb|left|320px|Hono louʻakau mo e matalaʻiʻakau]] Ko e '''tamaline''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia. ʻOku lava ʻo kai hono ngaahi ngeʻesi tenga.
==Hingoa ʻi he ngaahi lea kehe== *wiʻawaʻawa ([[lea fakahauaiʻi]]) *tamaligi ([[lea fakahaʻamoa]])
==Tataku== *Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī *Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward *Multipurpose trees for agroforestry in the Pacific islands; R.R. Thaman, C.R. Elevitch, K.M. Wilkinson *Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=peach |faitā=PrunusPersicaFlowers.jpg |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[rosales]] |familia= [[ROSACEAE]] |genus=Prunus |species=persica |fakamoʻoniʻanga= ([[Carolus Linnaeus|L.]]) [[August Johann Georg Karl Batsch|Batsch]] |fehokotaki= cs }} [[File:Flameprince peaches.jpg|left|200px|thumb|ko e ngaahi foʻi fua]] Ko e '''piisi''' ko e foʻi fua ia mei he fuʻu ʻakau lahi mo e hingoa tatau. Naʻe haʻu ʻa e foʻi lea ko ia, ko e pīsí, mei he [[lea fakapilitānia]].
He ʻaho ni ʻoku ngāueʻaki foki maʻa e ngaahi [[pī (ʻakau)|pī]], ''pea'' ʻi he lea fakapilitānia, kā ''peas'' kapau ʻoku lahi. Mahalo pe ʻoku sai ange ʻoku ui ʻa e ''peas'' ko e [[piʻisi]], kā ko e pī ʻe taha ia.
== Tataku == * Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī * Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward * Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name= |faitā= |faitālaulahi= 320px |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[fabales]] |familia= [[FABACEAE]] |genus=Maniltoa |tribus=detarieae |species=amicorum |fakamoʻoniʻanga=A.C. Smith }} Ko e '''pekepeka''' pe '''tamanu''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia, sai maʻa e tufunga.
==Ngaahi faʻahinga kehekehe== *tamanu: ʻoku ui foki ko e [[fetaʻu]] *tautauʻamanu; ko e hingoa ngāueʻaki ʻe Drake, mahalo pē ko e hala? Ko e [[langakali|tautauʻamanu]] ko e ʻakau kehe ia.
==Tataku== *Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī *Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward *Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 *Multipurpose trees for agroforestry in the Pacific islands; R.R. Thaman, C.R. Elevitch, K.M. Wilkinson *D.R. Drake et al., Rain forest vegetation of ʻEua Island, New Zealand {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=Southpacific maiten |faitā= |faitālaulahi= 320px |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[celastrales]] |familia= [[CELASTRACEAE]] |genus=Maytenus |species=vitiensis |fakamoʻoniʻanga= (A.Gray) [[Berthold_Carl_Seemann|Seem.]] }} Ko e '''olamaka''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia. ʻOku ui foki ko e ''Catha vitiensis'', ''Gymnosporia vitiensis'', mo e ''Gymnosporia samoensis''.
==Ngaahi faʻahinga kehekehe== *olamaka; koʻeni *olamaka = [[langakali]] vao = tautau-ʻa-manu = maʻamaʻalava, ''Elaeocarpus tonganus'' (ELAEOCARPACEAE) *olamaka = [[filimoto]] = [[kakalaʻuli]], ''Xylosma orbiculatum'' *olamaka, ''Canthium barbatum'' *olamaka, ''Psydrax odorata''
==Tataku== *http://cookislands.bishopmuseum.org/species.asp?id=6379 *Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī *Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward *Multipurpose trees for agroforestry in the Pacific islands; R.R. Thaman, C.R. Elevitch, K.M. Wilkinson *Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 *D.R. Drake et al., Rain forest vegetation of ʻEua Island, New Zealand Journal of Botany '''34''', 1996 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=Sting nettle tree |faitā= |faitālaulahi= 320px |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[rosales]] |familia= [[URTICACEAE]] |genus=Laportea |species=harveyi |fakamoʻoniʻanga= [[Berthold Carl Seemann|Seem.]] }} Ko e '''salato''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia. ʻOku lahi ʻene tupu ʻi [[ʻEua]], ʻoku siʻisiʻi pē ʻi he feituʻu kehe. ʻOku '''uʻu''' ho nima ʻe he lou salató, ʻoku faitoʻo ʻe heʻene toʻí. Ko hono ʻuhinga tatau ko e ''Dendrocnide harveyi''.
==Hingoa ʻi he ngaahi lea kehe== *salato ([[lea fakahaʻamoa]])
==Tataku== *Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī *Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward *Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 *D.R. Drake et al., Rain forest vegetation of ʻEua Island, New Zealand Journal of Botany '''34''', 1996 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name= |faitā= |faitālaulahi= 320px |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[celastrales]] (founga motuʻa) |familia= [[ICACINACEAE]] |genus=Citronella |species=samoensis |fakamoʻoniʻanga= (A.Gray) Howard }} Ko e '''olavai''' pe '''tutuna''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia. ʻOku tupu pē ʻi [[ʻEua]] (pea mo [[Haʻamoa]]). ʻOku manakoa ʻa hono foʻi fua ʻe he ngaahi manupuna. Ko hono ʻuhinga tatau: ''Villaresia samoensis''.
==Ngaahi faʻahinga kehekehe== *tutuna; vakai foki ki he [[koli]] mo e [[masi]] *tutuna, ''Psychotria insularum'' (RUBIACEAE) {wild island coffee}
==Hingoa ʻi he ngaahi lea kehe== *matalafi ([[lea fakahaʻamoa]]), ''Psychotria insularum'' *olavai ([[lea fakafutuna]])
