{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=White mulberry |faitā=Illustration Morus nigra0.jpg |faitālaulahi=240px |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[rosales]] |familia= [[MORACEAE]] |genus=Morus |species=alba |fakamoʻoniʻanga= [[Carolus Linnaeus|L.]] |fehokotaki= cs }} Ko e '''fuamelie''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia. ʻOku tātātaha ʻi Tongā ni. Mahalo pē ko e ngaahi faʻahinga ʻe tolu: '''fuamelie tea, fuamelie kula''' mo e '''fuamelie ʻuli''', ʻoku ʻikai kehe, ko e ngaahi fakakeheʻi pe fuo kehekehe pē. ʻOku lava ʻe tupu ʻa e fuʻu ʻakau foʻou mei he faʻahinga kehekehe ʻe ua (hybridisation).
== Ngaahi faʻahinga kehekehe == * fuamelie, fuamelie tea; koʻeni, ʻomi mei [[ʻĒsia]] hahake * fuamelie, fuamelie kula, ''Morus rubra'', ʻomi mei [[ʻAmelika]] tokelau hahake * fuamelie, fuamelie ʻuli, ''Morus nigra'', ʻomi mei [[ʻĒsia]] hahake (ʻasi ʻi he faitā) * fuamelie, ko e ngaahi foʻi [[kālepi]] mātuʻu
== Tataku == * Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī * Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward * Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name= |faitā=Omalanthusnutansearlwood.JPG |faitālaulahi= 320px |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[malpighiales]] |familia= [[EUPHORBIACEAE]] |tribus=hippomaneae |genus=Homalanthus |species=nutans |fakamoʻoniʻanga= ([[Georg Forster|G.Forst.]]) [[Jean Baptiste Antoine Guillemin|Guill.]] |fehokotaki= s l}} [[Image:Omalanthus nutans raceme.jpg|left|thumb|320px|''Omalanthus nutans'' raceme]] Ko e '''fonuamamala''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia. ʻOku lahi ʻene tupu ʻi [[ʻEua]]. ʻOku ui foki ko e ''H. pedicellatus''. ʻOku tohi foki ko e ''Omalanthus''. Naʻe tui ʻoku tatau ʻa e ngaahi fuʻu ʻakaú ni ʻi [[Polinisia]] hihifo mo e hahake, kā ʻoku tui het taimí ni, ʻoku na kehe. Ko e faʻahinga mei hahake (ʻotu motu [[Kuki]]) ko e ''H. moerenhoutianus'' ia.
==Hingoa ʻi he ngaahi lea kehe== *fanua mamala ([[lea fakahaʻamoa]]) *lepo ([[lea fakaʻuvea]]) *pata ([[lea fakafutuna]])
==Tataku== *http://cookislands.bishopmuseum.org/species.asp?id=6240 *Hokohoko ngaahi ʻakau; Vaʻa fekumi ngoue Vainī *Tongan dictionary; C.M. Churchward *Plants of Tonga; T.G. Yuncker; BPB bulletin '''220''', Honolulu 1959 *D.R. Drake et al., Rain forest vegetation of ʻEua Island, New Zealand Journal of Botany '''34''', 1996 {{potuʻi}}

{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=Red bead, red sandalwood tree |faitā=Adenanthera pavonina.jpg |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[fabales]] |familia= [[FABACEAE]] |tribus=mimoseae |genus=Adenanthera |species=pavonina |fakamoʻoniʻanga= [[Carolus Linnaeus|L.]] |fehokotaki= s }} Ko e '''lopa''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau lahi ia. Ko hono ngaahi foʻi tenga, ko e (foʻi) lopa, ʻoku ngāueʻaki he kula.
==Hingoa ʻi he ngaahi lea kehe== *huaʻulaʻula ([[lea fakahauaiʻi]]) *pomea ([[lea fakaniuē]]) *lopa ([[lea fakahaʻamoa]]) *mata kōviriviri, pitipitiʻō ([[lea fakakuki]]) *lera, lere damu, pomea, vaivai ([[lea fakafisi]])
