{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=Siberian motherwort, Lion's tail |faitā=Leonurus sibiricus.jpg |faitālaulahi= 280px |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[lamiales]] |familia= [[LAMIACEAE]] |genus=Leonurus |species=sibiricus |fakamoʻoniʻanga= [[Carolus Linnaeus|L.]] |fehokotaki= cs }} Ko e '''vavae tala''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau siʻi ia, ko e vao ia. Ko hingoa taʻefakalakanga ʻoʻona ia, mei he [[lea fakakuki]], ʻoku ʻikai ʻaupito ha [[vavae]], kā ʻoku kiʻi hangē mo e vavaekona ([[tuʻulapepe]]). ʻOku talatala hono ngaahi moto, kā ʻoku nau molu. ʻOku ui foki ko e ''Leonurus japonicus'' [[Maarten Houttuyn|Houtt.]], kae ʻoku pehē ʻe he kau saienisi ʻe niʻihi ko e faʻahinga kehe ia.
