{{Puha fakafaʻahinga |name=Common prickly pear |faitā=Opuntia monacantha.jpg |regnum= [[ʻakau]] |divisio= [[ʻakau matala]] |classis= [[lautengaʻiua]] |ordo= [[Caryophyllales]] |familia= [[CACTACEAE]] |genus=Opuntia |species=monacantha |fakamoʻoniʻanga= [[Adrian Hardy Haworth|Haw.]] |fehokotaki= cs }}
Ko e '''kakatisi''' ko e fuʻu ʻakau siʻi ia, ʻomi ki Tongá ni mei he fonua vevela mo mōmoa. Koʻeni mei he [[ʻAmelika]] tonga.
Ko e ʻakau talatala ia. ʻOku ui ko e kāinga ʻo e ngaahi kakatisi kotoa pē ''ʻakau kovi ʻoku mafola mo tupu vao'' ʻe he [[:Category:palemia ʻo Tonga|palemia]] ʻi 1926 (lao fakalahi 1988, vahe 128) maʻa Tonga kotoa pē. Neongo ia, ʻoku ʻiloʻi kinautolu ʻi he ngaahi ngoue Tonga ʻe niʻihi.
==Ngaahi faʻahinga kehekehe== *''Opuntia monacantha'', koʻeni *
